headline: Taiwan Voters Re-elect President in a Rebuke To Beijing’s Authority
abstract: The victory was a remarkable comeback for Ms. Tsai and suggested that Beijing’s pressure campaign had backfired.
lead_paragraph: TAIPEI, Taiwan — Taiwan’s voters delivered a stinging rebuke of China’s rising authoritarianism on Saturday by re-electing President Tsai Ing-wen, who vowed to preserve the island’s sovereignty in the face of Beijing’s intensifying efforts to bring it under its control.
